---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';

const lastReviewed = 'July 16, 2026';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Accessibility"
  kicker="Accessibility"
  lead="We want everyone to be able to read the group’s work. This statement describes the accessibility of this website, what we have done, and how to reach us if something is not working for you."
  description="Accessibility statement for the Kjolstad Lab website: conformance target, measures taken, known limitations, and how to report problems."
  headWidth="narrow"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow a11y flow">
      <h2>Conformance target</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        This site aims to conform to the
        {' '}<a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2, Level AA</a
        >. Accessibility was considered from the start of the design rather than added afterward.
      </p>

      <h2>What we have done</h2>
      <ul class="muted">
        <li>Semantic HTML with landmarks, a logical heading order, and a skip-to-content link.</li>
        <li>Full keyboard operation, visible focus indicators, and no keyboard traps.</li>
        <li>
          Colour is never the only way information is conveyed, and text and interface colours are
          chosen to meet AA contrast in both light and dark themes.
        </li>
        <li>A dark theme that respects your system preference and remembers an explicit choice.</li>
        <li>
          <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> is honoured; the hero animation stops and no content moves
          automatically.
        </li>
        <li>
          The publication explorer is keyboard-operable and announces its result count to assistive
          technology. With JavaScript disabled, the complete publication list is still available,
          grouped by year.
        </li>
        <li>
          Images have appropriate alternative text, and decorative graphics are hidden from
          assistive technology.
        </li>
        <li>
          Layouts remain usable at 200% zoom and with increased text spacing, and content reflows
          without horizontal scrolling at supported widths.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Testing</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        Pages were checked with automated tooling (axe-core, run through Playwright) and with manual
        review of keyboard operation, focus order, screen-reader names, zoom, and reduced-motion
        behaviour. Automated tools cannot catch every issue, so manual checks are part of our
        process.
      </p>

      <h2>Known limitations</h2>
      <ul class="muted">
        <li>
          Some links lead to PDFs and external sites (papers, code repositories, personal pages)
          that are not under our control and may not meet the same standard.
        </li>
        <li>
          The publication explorer’s live filtering requires JavaScript. Without it, the full list
          is shown but cannot be filtered interactively.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="muted">
        This statement does not claim full conformance; it describes our target and our current best
        effort. If you find a barrier we have missed, we would like to know.
      </p>

      <h2>Reporting a problem</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        If you encounter an accessibility barrier on this site, please email
        {' '}<a href={`mailto:${SITE.contact.email}?subject=Accessibility`}>{SITE.contact.email}</a
        >. Please describe the page and the problem, and we will do our best to address it.
      </p>

      <p class="a11y__date mono">Last reviewed: {lastReviewed}</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .a11y h2 {
    font-size: var(--step-1);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl) !important;
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2xs);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-hairline);
  }
  .a11y h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0 !important;
  }
  .a11y ul {
    padding-left: 1.2em;
  }
  .a11y li {
    margin-top: 0.5em;
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
  .a11y__date {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl) !important;
    padding-top: var(--space-m);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-hairline);
    color: var(--ink-subtle);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }
</style>
